### HowTo ###
# Assumptions: System starts in single user mode. 
# config-profile contains new configuration for IP address, hostname and NTP servers. 
# change-profile will search and replace previous configuration. 
# Modify change-profile and config-profile scripts before running them. 

### Typical usage in VMware environment ###
# Edit config-profile and change-profile 
# Change inittab to start system in single user mode on next boot
# Create OVA file and ship the VM

### !!Future Modifications?? ###
# Run this script after boot
# Force password changes
